<item>
            <title>[BEAM-8819] AvroCoder for SpecificRecords is not serialized correctly since 2.13.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-8819</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While trying to upgrade our pipelines from Beam 2.11.0 to Beam 2.16.0 we found that our SpecificRecords used in PCollection were being decoded as GenericRecords.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After some investigation we found the specific commit/issue that we think did brake it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/8342/files&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/pull/8342/files&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-7103&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-7103&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After the mentioned change all AvroCoders are serialized as simple urn: &quot;beam:coder:avro:v1&quot; which means they are deserialized / rehydrated as AvroCoder&amp;lt;GenericRecord&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
